snippet.textDisplay:
Absolutely beautiful and talented !!! Absolutely mesmerising !!! Here we have three 'soulsters' of the organic kind ... their voices and their instruments ... long before producers feature in the equation ... and all without simulated-and-machine-generated ugly-and-heavy beats !!! Dears Bill, Stevie and John are the kind of soul gents (besides Uncle's isaac Hayes) that for some of us are an absolute pleasure to listen to, in the fullness of their organic talents.

And art we noticing the resemblence between the younger Bill Withers and John Legend? Just give dear John Legend a bit of a 'modest afro' and one canst actually see a Bill Withers of The 70s.

And then dear Stevie's 'Wonder'ful vocal dexterity that is injected into this number ... Oh GOD bless these three beautiful men, and may Bill Withers himself rest in peace after all the decades of pure music he has given the world !!!

We shalt never forget thee Mr Withers-called-William who has travelled unto the place as Isaac Hayes !!!

Dear Rock & Roll Hall of Fame .... as a publisher, we thank thee !!!

snippet.textDisplay: For anyone saying that John didn't let Bill sing his own song. These things are planned and rehearsed, it's not like John surprisingly just took over. Bill Withers clearly had a reason he could not perform the whole song, may he rest in piece. John was trying to help him out the best way he could, he was also probably nervous performing next to his idols. You can also see Bill keeping the mic very far away and not singing much, maybe he couldn't find the key or something. But come on, John did a great job, and Stevie was amazing as usual.

snippet.textDisplay: Bill Withers recorded some of the most meaningful songs of all time, 'Lean on Me',' Ain't no sunshine when you're gone', 'Just the Two of Us'  and 'Lovely Day. Bill may have passed away, but his influence and the beauty of his memory in his music will never fade. RIP, Bill. Your albums in my collection were always precious, now even more so.
